President Obama has announced his intent to nominate Nanci E. Langley as Commissioner of the Postal Regulatory Commission and Howard A. Shelanski as Administrator of the Office of Information and Regulatory Affairs, Office of Management and Budget. Langley is currently a Commissioner of the Postal Regulatory Commission and has previous experience in government relations and legislative assistance. Shelanski is the Director of the Bureau of Economics at the Federal Trade Commission and has a background in law and economics. President Obama expressed his confidence in their abilities and looks forward to working with them in the future.